{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81a11390-efea-4f04-9246-ba34bda547bc","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to **MSTest v3**:\n\n### 1. **Project file (`TestProject.csproj`)**\n- **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces the old `MSTest.TestAdapter` + `MSTest.TestFramework` combo)\n- **Update** the target framework (net462 is unsupported by MSTest v3; minimum is `net6.0`)\n\n### 2. **Test code (`OrderServiceTests.cs`)**\n- The `using` stays the same (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`) — MSTest v3 preserves that namespace.\n- Your `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and `Assert` calls are all compatible — **no code changes needed**.\n\n### Summary of `.csproj` changes\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n\n<!-- Update -->\n<TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />\n```\n\nWant me to apply these changes and verify the project builds and tests pass?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0533ed37-18f7-451e-88c1-6044c3ca64b4","outputTokens":375},"id":"5a8224f5-5b40-415f-81d7-64f8929bf5a3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:06:08.920Z","parentId":"2500ec45-2eab-4c22-914b-5d8bf281cea6"}
